01Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hello,\r\nconsider this code example:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![deny(missing_docs)]\r\n#![deny(missing_doc_code_examples)]\r\n//! crate level doc\r\n//! ```\r\n//! println!(\"hello\"):\r\n//! ```\r\n\r\n\r\n/// doc\r\n///\r\n/// ```\r\n/// println!(\"hello\");\r\n/// ```\r\nfn test() {\r\n}\r\n\r\n// the allow() here works as expected, but missing_doc_code_examples still complains\r\n#[allow(missing_docs)]\r\nmod module1 {\r\n\r\n  fn test() {}\r\n}\r\n\r\n// here we want some docs but no code examples, but missing_doc_code_examples still complains\r\n#[allow(missing_doc_code_examples)]\r\n/// doc\r\nmod module2 {\r\n\r\n  /// doc\r\n  fn test() {}\r\n}\r\n\r\n/// doc\r\n///\r\n/// ```\r\n/// println!(\"hello\");\r\n/// ```\r\nmod module3 {\r\n\r\n  // here we want some code examples but missing_doc_code_examples does not complain\r\n  /// doc\r\n  fn test() {}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere I would expect the following behaviour when running `cargo doc`:\r\n- `module1` has `allow(missing_docs)` so `missing_doc_code_examples` should be silent\r\n- `module2` has `allow(missing_doc_code_examples)` yet we still get errors for missing docs on `module2`, I think we should not\r\n- `module3` has a code example, but `module3::test` does not, we should get an error for the missing example on `module3::test`\r\n\r\ncc @GuillaumeGomez ", "closed_by": {"login": "GuillaumeGomez", "id": 3050060, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwNTAwNjA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3050060?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez", "html_url": "https://github.com/GuillaumeGomez", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeGomez/sta